**Example: Feedback Collection and Analysis Application**

Let's create a complete, end-to-end application that collects feedback from users, stores it in a database, and analyzes it to provide insights for social work.

**Database Design:**

We'll use a relational database to store feedback data. The database will have the following tables:

* `users`: stores user information (name, email, etc.)
* `feedback`: stores feedback data (text, rating, etc.)
* `categories`: stores categories for feedback (e.g. "suggestions", "complaints", etc.)

**Database Schema:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE feedback (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  category_id INT,
  text TEXT,
  rating INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id),
  FOREIGN KEY (category_id) REFERENCES categories(id)
);

CREATE TABLE categories (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255)
);
```
**Frontend Code:**

We'll use JavaScript, HTML, and CSS to create a frontend application that collects feedback from users.

**HTML:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Feedback Collection and Analysis</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Feedback Collection and Analysis</h1>
  <form id="feedback-form">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
    <label for="category">Category:</label>
    <select id="category" name="category">
      <option value="1">Suggestions</option>
      <option value="2">Complaints</option>
      <option value="3">Other</option>
    </select><br><br>
    <label for="text">Text:</label>
    <textarea id="text" name="text"></textarea><br><br>
    <label for="rating">Rating:</label>
    <select id="rating" name="rating">
      <option value="1">1</option>
      <option value="2">2</option>
      <option value="3">3</option>
      <option value="4">4</option>
      <option value="5">5</option>
    </select><br><br>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
  </form>
  <div id="result"></div>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
